FBIS4-14832 "drsov065_v_94004" FBIS-SOV-94-065 Daily Report 31 Mar 1994 Lithuania `Polonia' Channel Replacing Polish First Program `Polonia' Channel Replacing Polish First Program WS0504091694 Vilnius ELTA in Lithuanian 1238 GMT 31 Mar 94 WS0504091694 Vilnius ELTA Lithuanian BFN [Text] As of 4 April 1994, Lithuania will begin airing the "Polonia" station instead of the first Polish television channel. This decision was adopted by the Council of the Baltic Television which relays programs of neighboring countries, because Polish television did not resolve the copyright problem and could not continue broadcasting its first channel, but proposed to transmit the satellite station "Polonia."
